{
  "doc_id": "16108",
  "text": "The structure of E. coli L11 (EcL11) was taken from the Protein Data Bank (PDB ID 2AWB) [CITATION_1] . In the case of S. cerevisiae L12 (ScL12), the PDB file was 1K5Y (3). In this file, the structure of ScL12 presents only C alpha atoms; the remaining main and side chains were taken from the file 1S1I [CITATION_2] . The structure of RNA GAR domain was also taken from the 1S1I file, from Haloarcula marismortui, and was mutated into the one corresponding to S. cerevisiae. Finally, the structure of thiostrepton was extracted from the file 1OLN [CITATION_3] . With all these elements, the two ternary complexes were assembled as follows: using 1S1I as a template EcL11, ScL12 and RNA GAR domain were superimposed on their counterparts and the coordinates of thiostrepton were then exported. For comparative reasons, EcL11-EcGAR complex 2AW4 from E. coli was also considered (44).",
